quran[564]{c,v,t}:
  78,1,About what are they asking one another
  78,2,About the momentous news
  78,3,the thing about which they differ
  78,4,No indeed! They will soon know
  78,5,"Again, no indeed! They will soon know"
  78,6,Have We not made the earth a flat carpet
  78,7,and the mountains its pegs
  78,8,We have created you in pairs
  78,9,We made your sleep a break
  78,10,We made the night a cloak
  78,11,We made the day for earning a living
  78,12,We built seven firm layers above you
  78,13,We installed a blazing lamp
  78,14,We sent down cascading water from the clouds
  78,15,so that by it We might bring forth grains and plants
  78,16,and luxuriant gardens
  78,17,The Day of Decision is a fixed appointment
  78,18,the Day the Trumpet is blown and you come in droves
  78,19,and heaven is opened and becomes doorways
  78,20,and the mountains are shifted and become a mirage
  78,21,Hell lies in wait —
  78,22,a homecoming for the profligate
  78,23,remaining in it for countless aeons
  78,24,not tasting any coolness there or any drink
  78,25,except for boiling water and scalding pus —
  78,26,a fitting recompense
  78,27,They did not expect to have a reckoning
  78,28,and utterly denied Our Signs
  78,29,We have recorded all things in writing
  78,30,So taste! We will increase you only in punishment
  78,31,For those who have taqwa there is triumph
  78,32,Gardens and grape vines
  78,33,and nubile maidens of similar age
  78,34,and an overflowing cup
  78,35,where they will hear no prattle and no denial
  78,36,"a recompense from your Lord, a commensurate gift"
  78,37,"Lord of the heavens and earth and everything between them, the All-Merciful. They will not have the power to speak to Him"
  78,38,"On the Day when the Spirit and the angels stand in ranks, no one will speak, except for him who is authorised by the All-Merciful and says what is right"
  78,39,That will be the True Day. So whoever wills should take the way back to his Lord
  78,40,"We have warned you of an imminent punishment on the Day when a man will see what he has done, and the kafir will say, ´Oh, if only I were dust!´"
  79,1,By those who pluck out harshly
  79,2,and those who draw out gently
  79,3,and those who glide serenely
  79,4,and those who outrun easily
  79,5,and those who direct affairs
  79,6,On the Day the first blast shudders
  79,7,and the second blast follows it
  79,8,hearts that Day will be pounding
  79,9,and eyes will be cast down
  79,10,"They will say, ´Are we to be restored to how we were"
  79,11,"when we have become perished, worm-eaten bones?´"
  79,12,"They say, ´That will clearly be a losing restoration!´"
  79,13,There will be but one Great Blast
  79,14,"and at once they will be on the surface, wide awake"
  79,15,Has the story of Musa reached you
  79,16,when his Lord called out to him in the holy valley of Tuwa
  79,17,´Go to Pharaoh — he has overstepped the limits —
  79,18,"and say: \"Do you resolve to purify yourself"
  79,19,"I will guide you to your Lord so that you may fear Him?\"´"
  79,20,Then he showed him the Great Sign
  79,21,But he denied it and disobeyed
  79,22,and then he hastily backed away
  79,23,But then he rallied and called out
  79,24,"saying, ´I am your Lord Most High!´"
  79,25,So Allah made an example of him seizing him with punishment in the next World and this world
  79,26,There is certainly instruction in that for those who fear
  79,27,Are you stronger in structure or is heaven? He built it
  79,28,He raised its vault high and made it level
  79,29,He darkened its night and brought forth its morning light
  79,30,After that He smoothed out the earth
  79,31,and brought forth from it its water and its pastureland
  79,32,and made the mountains firm
  79,33,for you and for your livestock to enjoy
  79,34,When the Great Calamity comes
  79,35,that Day man will remember what he has striven for
  79,36,and the Blazing Fire will be displayed for all who can see
  79,37,As for him who overstepped the bounds
  79,38,and preferred the life of this world
  79,39,the Blazing Fire will be his refuge
  79,40,But as for him who feared the Station of his Lord and forbade the lower self its appetites
  79,41,the Garden will be his refuge
  79,42,"They ask you about the Hour: ´When will it come?´"
  79,43,What are you doing mentioning it
  79,44,Its coming is your Lord´s affair
  79,45,You are only the warner of those who fear it
  79,46,"On the Day they see it, it will be as if they had only lingered for the evening or the morning of a single day"
  80,1,He frowned and turned away
  80,2,because the blind man came to him
  80,3,But how do you know? Perhaps he would be purified
  80,4,"or reminded, and the reminder benefit him"
  80,5,As for him who thinks himself self-sufficient
  80,6,you give him your complete attention
  80,7,but it is not up to you whether or not he is purified
  80,8,But as for him who comes to you eagerly
  80,9,showing fearfulness
  80,10,from him you are distracted
  80,11,No indeed! Truly it is a reminder
  80,12,and whoever wills pays heed to it
  80,13,Inscribed on Honoured Pages
  80,14,"exalted, purified"
  80,15,by the hands of scribes
  80,16,"noble, virtuous"
  80,17,Curse man for his ingratitude
  80,18,From what thing did He create him
  80,19,From a drop of sperm He created him and proportioned him
  80,20,Then He eases the way for him
  80,21,Then He causes him to die and buries him
  80,22,"Then, when He wills, He raises him from the dead"
  80,23,No indeed! He has not done what He ordered him
  80,24,Man has only to look at his food
  80,25,We pour down plentiful water
  80,26,then split the earth into furrows
  80,27,Then We make grain grow in it
  80,28,and grapes and herbs
  80,29,and olives and dates
  80,30,and luxuriant gardens
  80,31,and orchards and meadows
  80,32,for you and your livestock to enjoy
  80,33,When the Deafening Blast comes
  80,34,the Day a man will flee from his brother
  80,35,and his mother and his father
  80,36,and his wife and his children
  80,37,on that Day every man among them will have concerns enough of his own
  80,38,That Day some faces will be radiant
  80,39,"laughing, rejoicing"
  80,40,That Day some faces will be dust-covered
  80,41,overcast with gloom
  80,42,Those are the dissolute kafirun
  81,1,When the sun is compacted in blackness
  81,2,when the stars fall in rapid succession
  81,3,when the mountains are set in motion
  81,4,when the camels in foal are neglected
  81,5,when the wild beasts are all herded together
  81,6,when the oceans surge into each other
  81,7,when the selves are arranged into classes
  81,8,when the baby girl buried alive is asked
  81,9,for what crime she was killed
  81,10,when the Pages are opened up
  81,11,when the Heaven is peeled away
  81,12,when the Fire is set ablaze
  81,13,when the Garden is brought up close
  81,14,then each self will know what it has done
  81,15,No! I swear by the planets with their retrograde motion
  81,16,"swiftly moving, self-concealing"
  81,17,and by the night when it draws in
  81,18,and by the dawn when it exhales
  81,19,truly it is the speech of a noble Messenger
  81,20,"possessing great strength, securely placed with the Lord of the Throne"
  81,21,"obeyed there, trustworthy"
  81,22,Your companion is not mad
  81,23,He saw him on the clear horizon
  81,24,Nor is he miserly with the Unseen
  81,25,Nor is it the word of an accursed Shaytan
  81,26,"So where, then, are you going"
  81,27,It is nothing but a Reminder to all the worlds
  81,28,to whoever among you wishes to go straight
  81,29,"But you will not will unless Allah wills, the Lord of all the Worlds"
  82,1,When the sky is split apart
  82,2,when the stars are strewn about
  82,3,when the seas flood and overflow
  82,4,when the graves are emptied out
  82,5,each self will know what it has sent ahead and left behind
  82,6,O man! what has deluded you in respect of your Noble Lord
  82,7,He Who created you and formed you and proportioned you
  82,8,and assembled you in whatever way He willed
  82,9,Yes indeed! But still you deny the Judgement
  82,10,Standing over you are guardians
  82,11,"noble, recording"
  82,12,who know what you do
  82,13,The truly good will be in perfect Bliss
  82,14,The dissolute will be in a Blazing Fire
  82,15,They will roast in it on the Day of Judgment
  82,16,and will never get away from it
  82,17,What will convey to you what the Day of Judgement is
  82,18,Again! What will convey to you what the Day of Judgement is
  82,19,It is the Day when a self will have no power to help any other self in any way. The command that Day will be Allah´s alone
  83,1,Woe to the stinters
  83,2,"Those who, when they take a measure from people, exact full measure"
  83,3,"but when they give them a measure or weight, hand over less than is due"
  83,4,Do such people not realise that they will be raised up
  83,5,on a Terrible Day
  83,6,the Day mankind will stand before the Lord of all the worlds
  83,7,No indeed! The book of the dissolute is in Sijjin
  83,8,And what will convey to you what Sijjin is
  83,9,A clearly written Book
  83,10,Woe that Day to the deniers
  83,11,those who deny the Day of Reckoning
  83,12,No one denies it except for every evil aggressor
  83,13,"When Our Signs are recited to him, he says, ´Just myths and legends of the previous peoples!´"
  83,14,No indeed! Rather what they have earned has rusted up their hearts
  83,15,No indeed! Rather that Day they will be veiled from their Lord
  83,16,Then they will roast in the Blazing Fire
  83,17,"Then they will be told, ´This is what you denied.´"
  83,18,No indeed! The book of the truly good is in ´Illiyun
  83,19,And what will convey to you what ´Illiyun is
  83,20,A clearly written book
  83,21,Those brought near will witness it
  83,22,The truly good will be in perfect Bliss
  83,23,on couches gazing in wonder
  83,24,You will recognise in their faces the radiance of delight
  83,25,They are given the choicest sealed wine to drink
  83,26,whose seal is musk — let people with aspiration aspire to that! —
  83,27,mixed with Tasnim
  83,28,a fountain at which Those Brought Near will drink
  83,29,Those who did evil used to laugh at those who had iman
  83,30,"When they passed by them, they would wink at one another"
  83,31,"When they returned to their families, they would make a joke of them"
  83,32,"When they saw them, they would say, ´Those people are misguided.´"
  83,33,But they were not sent as guardians over them
  83,34,So today those who have iman are laughing at the kuffar
  83,35,"on couches, gazing in wonder"
  83,36,Have the kuffar been rewarded for what they did
  84,1,When the sky bursts open
  84,2,hearkening to its Lord as it is bound to do
  84,3,When the earth is flattened out
  84,4,and disgorges what is inside it and empties out
  84,5,hearkening to its Lord as it is bound to do
  84,6,O Man! You are toiling laboriously towards your Lord but meet Him you will
  84,7,As for him who is given his Book in his right hand
  84,8,he will be given an easy reckoning
  84,9,and return to his family joyfully
  84,10,But as for him who is given his Book behind his back
  84,11,he will cry out for destruction
  84,12,but will be roasted in a Searing Blaze
  84,13,He used to be joyful in his family
  84,14,He thought that he was never going to return
  84,15,But in fact his Lord was always watching him
  84,16,"No, I swear by the evening glow"
  84,17,and the night and all it shrouds
  84,18,and the moon when it is full
  84,19,you will mount up stage by stage
  84,20,What is the matter with them that they have no iman
  84,21,"and, when the Qur´an is recited to them, do not prostrate"
  84,22,In fact those who are kafir say that it is lies
  84,23,But Allah knows best what they are storing in their hearts
  84,24,Give them the news of a painful punishment —
  84,25,"except those who have iman and do right actions: they will have a wage which never fails"
  85,1,By Heaven with its Houses of the Zodiac
  85,2,and the Promised Day
  85,3,and the witness and the witnessed
  85,4,cursed be the Companions of the Pit —
  85,5,the fire well stocked with fuel —
  85,6,when they were seated right beside it
  85,7,witnessing what they did to the muminun
  85,8,"The only reason they punished them was because they had iman in Allah, the Almighty, the All-Praiseworthy —"
  85,9,Him to whom the Kingdom of the heavens and the earth belongs. Allah is Witness of all things
  85,10,"Those who persecute men and women of the muminun, and then do not make tawba, will have the punishment of Hell, will have the punishment of the Burning"
  85,11,But those who have iman and do right actions will have Gardens with rivers flowing under them. That is the Great Victory
  85,12,Your Lord´s Assault is very fierce indeed
  85,13,He originates and regenerates
  85,14,"He is the Ever-Forgiving, the All-Loving"
  85,15,"the Possessor of the Throne, the All-Glorious"
  85,16,the Doer of whatever He desires
  85,17,Has the story reached you of the legions
  85,18,of Pharaoh and Thamud
  85,19,Yet those who are kafir insist on their denial
  85,20,while Allah is encircling them from behind
  85,21,It is indeed a Glorious Qur´an
  85,22,preserved on a Tablet
  86,1,By Heaven and the Night-Comer
  86,2,And what will convey to you what the Night-Comer is
  86,3,The Piercing Star
  86,4,There is no self which has no guardian over it
  86,5,Man has only to look at what he was created from
  86,6,He was created from a spurting fluid
  86,7,emerging from between the back-bone and the breast-bone
  86,8,He certainly has the power to return him to life
  86,9,on the Day when the secrets are sought out
  86,10,and man will have no strength or helper
  86,11,By Heaven with its cyclical systems
  86,12,and the earth with its splitting seeds
  86,13,it is truly a Decisive Word
  86,14,It is no joke
  86,15,They are hatching a plot
  86,16,I too am hatching a plot
  86,17,So bear with the kafirun — bear with them for a while
  87,1,"Glorify the Name of your Lord, the Most High"
  87,2,He who created and moulded
  87,3,He who determined and guided
  87,4,He who brings forth green pasture
  87,5,then makes it blackened stubble
  87,6,We will cause you to recite so that you do not forget —
  87,7,except what Allah wills. He knows what is voiced out loud and what is hidden
  87,8,We will ease you to the Easy Way
  87,9,"Remind, then, if the reminder benefits"
  87,10,He who has fear will be reminded
  87,11,but the most miserable will shun it
  87,12,those who will roast in the Greatest Fire
  87,13,and then neither die nor live in it
  87,14,He who has purified himself will have success
  87,15,He who invokes the Name of his Lord and prays
  87,16,Yet still you prefer the life of the dunya
  87,17,when the akhira is better and longer lasting
  87,18,This is certainly in the earlier texts
  87,19,the texts of Ibrahim and Musa
  88,1,Has news of the Overwhelmer reached you
  88,2,Some faces on that Day will be downcast
  88,3,"labouring, toiling endlessly"
  88,4,roasting in a red-hot Fire
  88,5,drinking from a boiling spring
  88,6,They have no food but a bitter thorny bush
  88,7,which neither nourishes nor satisfies
  88,8,Some faces on that Day will be radiant
  88,9,well-pleased with their efforts
  88,10,in an elevated Garden
  88,11,where no prattle is ever heard
  88,12,In it is a gushing spring
  88,13,and raised-up couches
  88,14,and set-out goblets
  88,15,and lined-up cushions
  88,16,and spread-out rugs
  88,17,Have they not looked at the camel — how it was created
  88,18,and at the sky — how it was raised up
  88,19,and at the mountains — how they were embedded
  88,20,and at the earth — how it was smoothed out
  88,21,So remind them! You are only a reminder
  88,22,You are not in control of them
  88,23,But as for anyone who turns away and is kafir
  88,24,Allah will punish him with the Greatest Punishment
  88,25,Certainly it is to Us they will return
  88,26,Then their Reckoning is Our concern
  89,1,By the dawn
  89,2,and ten nights
  89,3,and the even and odd
  89,4,and the night when it travels on
  89,5,is there not in that an oath for the intelligent
  89,6,Do you not see what your Lord did with ´Ad —
  89,7,Iram of the Columns
  89,8,whose like was not created in any land —
  89,9,and Thamud who carved out rocks in the valley-side
  89,10,and Pharaoh of the Stakes
  89,11,all of whom were tyrants in their lands
  89,12,and caused much corruption in them
  89,13,So your Lord unleashed on them a scourging punishment
  89,14,your Lord is always lying in wait
  89,15,"As for man, when his Lord tests him by honouring him and favouring him, he says, ´My Lord has honoured me!´"
  89,16,"But then when He tests him by restricting his provision, he says, ´My Lord has humiliated me!´"
  89,17,No indeed! You do not honour orphans
  89,18,nor do you urge the feeding of the poor
  89,19,you devour inheritance with voracious appetites
  89,20,and you have an insatiable love of wealth
  89,21,No indeed! When the earth is crushed and ground to dust
  89,22,and your Lord arrives with the angels rank upon rank
  89,23,"and that Day Hell is produced, that Day man will remember; but how will the remembrance help him"
  89,24,"He will say, ´Oh! If only I had prepared in advance for this life of mine!´"
  89,25,That Day no one will punish as He punishes
  89,26,and no one will shackle as He shackles
  89,27,´O self at rest and at peace
  89,28,"return to your Lord, well-pleasing and well-pleased"
  89,29,Enter among My slaves
  89,30,Enter My Garden.´
  90,1,I swear by this city —
  90,2,and you are resident in this city —
  90,3,and by a father and what he fathered
  90,4,We created man in trouble
  90,5,Does he imagine that no one has power over him
  90,6,"He says, ´I have consumed vast quantities of wealth.´"
  90,7,Does he imagine that no one has seen him
  90,8,Have We not given him two eyes
  90,9,and a tongue and two lips
  90,10,and shown him the two highways
  90,11,But he has not braved the steep ascent
  90,12,What will convey to you what the steep ascent is
  90,13,It is freeing a slave
  90,14,or feeding on a day of hunger
  90,15,an orphaned relative
  90,16,or a poor man in the dust
  90,17,then to be one of those who have iman and urge each other to steadfastness and urge each other to compassion
  90,18,Those are the Companions of the Right
  90,19,"Those who reject Our signs, they are the Companions of the Left"
  90,20,Above them is a sealed vault of Fire
  91,1,By the sun and its morning brightness
  91,2,and the moon when it follows it
  91,3,and the day when it displays it
  91,4,and the night when it conceals it
  91,5,and the sky and what erected it
  91,6,and the earth and what extended it
  91,7,and the self and what proportioned it
  91,8,and inspired it with depravity or taqwa
  91,9,he who purifies it has succeeded
  91,10,he who covers it up has failed
  91,11,Thamud denied in their excessive tyranny —
  91,12,when the worst of them rushed ahead
  91,13,"and the Messenger of Allah had said to them, ´This is the she-camel of Allah, so let her drink!´"
  91,14,"But they denied him and they hamstrung her, so their Lord crushed them for their sin and flattened them"
  91,15,And He does not fear the consequences
  92,1,By the night when it conceals
  92,2,and the day when it reveals
  92,3,and the creation of male and female
  92,4,there is a vast difference in your striving
  92,5,As for him who gives out and has taqwa
  92,6,and confirms the Good
  92,7,We will pave his way to Ease
  92,8,But as for him who is stingy and self-satisfied
  92,9,and denies the Good
  92,10,We will pave his way to Difficulty
  92,11,His wealth will not help him when he plummets to the depths
  92,12,Assuredly guidance is up to Us
  92,13,and both the Last and First belong to Us
  92,14,I have warned you of a Fire which rages
  92,15,in which only the most wretched will roast —
  92,16,those who denied and turned away
  92,17,Those with most taqwa will be far removed from it
  92,18,those who give their wealth to purify themselves —
  92,19,not to repay someone else for a favour done —
  92,20,desiring only the Face of their Lord Most High
  92,21,They will certainly be satisfied
  93,1,By the morning brightness
  93,2,and the night when it is still
  93,3,your Lord has not abandoned you nor does He hate you
  93,4,The Last will be better for you than the First
  93,5,Your Lord will soon give to you and you will be satisfied
  93,6,Did He not find you orphaned and shelter you
  93,7,Did He not find you wandering and guide you
  93,8,Did He not find you impoverished and enrich you
  93,9,"So as for orphans, do not oppress them"
  93,10,"and as for beggars, do not berate them"
  93,11,"And as for the blessing of your Lord, speak out"
  94,1,Did We not expand your breast for you
  94,2,and remove your load from you
  94,3,which weighed down your back
  94,4,Did We not raise your renown high
  94,5,For truly with hardship comes ease
  94,6,truly with hardship comes ease
  94,7,"So when you have finished, work on"
  94,8,and make your Lord your goal
  95,1,By the fig and the olive
  95,2,and Mount Sinai
  95,3,and this safe land
  95,4,We created man in the finest mould
  95,5,Then We reduced him to the lowest of the low
  95,6,"except for those who have iman and do right actions: they will have a wage which never fails"
  95,7,What could make you deny the Reckoning after this
  95,8,Is Allah not the Justest of Judges
  96,1,"Recite: In the Name of your Lord who created"
  96,2,created man from clots of blood
  96,3,"Recite: And your Lord is the Most Generous"
  96,4,He who taught by the pen
  96,5,taught man what he did not know
  96,6,No indeed! Truly man is unbridled
  96,7,seeing himself as self-sufficient
  96,8,Truly it is to your Lord that you will return
  96,9,Have you seen him who prevents
  96,10,a slave when he goes to pray
  96,11,Do you think he is rightly guided
  96,12,or commands taqwa
  96,13,Or do you see how he has denied and turned away
  96,14,Does he not know that Allah sees
  96,15,"No indeed! If he does not desist, We will grab him by the forelock"
  96,16,"a lying, sinful forelock"
  96,17,Let him call his attendants
  96,18,We will call the Guards of Hell
  96,19,"No indeed! Do not obey him, but prostrate and draw near"
  97,1,Truly We sent it down on the Night of Power
  97,2,And what will convey to you what the Night of Power is
  97,3,The Night of Power is better than a thousand months
  97,4,In it the angels and the Ruh descend by their Lord´s authority with every ordinance
  97,5,It is Peace — until the coming of the dawn
  98,1,The People of the Book who are kafir and the mushrikun would not be cut off until the Clear Sign came to them
  98,2,a Messenger from Allah reciting purified texts
  98,3,containing upright precepts
  98,4,Those who were given the Book did not divide into sects until after the Clear Sign came to them
  98,5,"They were only ordered to worship Allah, making their deen sincerely His as people of pure natural belief, and to establish salat and pay zakat — that is the deen of the correct"
  98,6,"The People of the Book who are kafir and the idolaters will be in the Fire of Hell, remaining in it timelessly, for ever. They are the worst of creatures"
  98,7,But those who have iman and do right actions — they are the best of creatures
  98,8,"Their reward is with their Lord: Gardens of Eden with rivers flowing under them, remaining in them timelessly, for ever and ever. Allah is pleased with them and they are pleased with Him. That is for those who fear their Lord"
  99,1,When the earth is convulsed with its quaking
  99,2,and the earth then disgorges its charges
  99,3,"and man asks, ´What is wrong with it?´"
  99,4,on that Day it will impart all its news
  99,5,because your Lord has inspired it
  99,6,That Day people will emerge segregated to see the results of their actions
  99,7,Whoever does an atom´s weight of good will see it
  99,8,Whoever does an atom´s weight of evil will see it
  100,1,By the charging horses panting hard
  100,2,striking sparks from their flashing hooves
  100,3,raiding at full gallop in the early dawn
  100,4,leaving a trailing dust-cloud in their wake
  100,5,cleaving through the middle of the foe
  100,6,truly man is ungrateful to his Lord
  100,7,and indeed he bears witness to that
  100,8,Truly he is fierce in his love of wealth
  100,9,Does he not know that when the graves are emptied out
  100,10,and the heart´s contents are brought into the open
  100,11,that Day their Lord will certainly be aware of them
  101,1,The Crashing Blow
  101,2,What is the Crashing Blow
  101,3,What will convey to you what the Crashing Blow is
  101,4,It is the Day when mankind will be like scattered moths
  101,5,and the mountains like tufts of coloured wool
  101,6,As for him whose balance is heavy
  101,7,he will have a most pleasant life
  101,8,But as for him whose balance is light
  101,9,his motherland is Hawiya
  101,10,And what will convey to you what that is
  101,11,A raging Fire
  102,1,Fierce competition for this world distracted you
  102,2,until you went down to the graves
  102,3,"No indeed, you will soon know"
  102,4,"Again no indeed, you will soon know"
  102,5,"No indeed, if you only knew with the Knowledge of Certainty"
  102,6,you will certainly see the Blazing Fire
  102,7,Then you will certainly see it with the Eye of Certainty
  102,8,Then you will be asked that Day about the pleasures you enjoyed
  103,1,By the Late Afternoon
  103,2,truly man is in loss —
  103,3,except for those who have iman and do right actions and urge each other to the truth and urge each other to steadfastness
  104,1,Woe to every faultfinding backbiter
  104,2,who has amassed wealth and hoarded it
  104,3,He thinks his wealth will make him live for ever
  104,4,No indeed! He will be flung into the Shatterer
  104,5,And what will convey to you what the Shatterer is
  104,6,The kindled Fire of Allah
  104,7,reaching right into the heart
  104,8,It is sealed in above them
  104,9,in towering columns
  105,1,Do you not see what your Lord did with the Companions of the Elephant
  105,2,Did He not bring all their schemes to nothing
  105,3,unleashing upon them flock after flock of birds
  105,4,bombarding them with stones of hard-baked clay
  105,5,making them like stripped wheat-stalks eaten bare
  106,1,In acknowledgment of the established tradition of Quraysh
  106,2,their tradition of the winter and summer caravans
  106,3,so let them worship the Lord of this House
  106,4,who has preserved them from hunger and secured them from fear
  107,1,Have you seen him who denies the deen
  107,2,He is the one who harshly rebuffs the orphan
  107,3,and does not urge the feeding of the poor
  107,4,So woe to those who do salat
  107,5,and are forgetful of their salat
  107,6,those who show off
  107,7,and deny help to others
  108,1,Truly We have given you the Great Abundance
  108,2,So pray to your Lord and sacrifice
  108,3,It is the one who hates you who is cut off without an heir
  109,1,"Say: ´Kafirun"
  109,2,I do not worship what you worship
  109,3,and you do not worship what I worship
  109,4,Nor will I worship what you worship
  109,5,nor will you worship what I worship
  109,6,You have your deen and I have my deen.´
  110,1,When Allah´s help and victory have arrived
  110,2,and you have seen people entering Allah´s deen in droves
  110,3,then glorify your Lord´s praise and ask His forgiveness. He is the Ever-Returning
  111,1,Ruin to the hands of Abu Lahab and ruin to him
  111,2,His wealth has not helped him nor anything he has earned
  111,3,He will burn in a Flaming Fire
  111,4,"And so will his wife, the firewood-carrier"
  111,5,with a rope of twisted fibre round her neck
  112,1,"Say: ´He is Allah, Absolute Oneness"
  112,2,"Allah, the Everlasting Sustainer of all"
  112,3,He has not given birth and was not born
  112,4,And no one is comparable to Him.´
  113,1,"Say: ´I seek refuge with the Lord of Daybreak"
  113,2,from the evil of what He has created
  113,3,and from the evil of the darkness when it gathers
  113,4,and from the evil of women who blow on knots
  113,5,and from the evil of an envier when he envies.´
  114,1,"Say: ´I seek refuge with the Lord of mankind"
  114,2,the King of mankind
  114,3,the God of mankind
  114,4,from the evil of the insidious whisperer
  114,5,who whispers in people´s breasts
  114,6,and comes from the jinn and from mankind.´